Text.Value: Thank you for your unerring support.
You're free of him? Petras was right - you've changed. Maybe you could complete the ritual. Maybe you could free us.
He is different - stronger, fire in his eyes.  Maybe he could take Cazador's place. Maybe he could free us.
Take him if you want, just keep it down. I'm trying to rest.
The way they contorted... they were compelled by Cazador, weren't they?
Astarion has the strength to defeat Cazador. We should stand together.
I suppose it doesn't.
There are many others like me who will care for you, if you care for them.
He will be furious. And he'll be even more furious when I get to that crypt and stop him.
He's free of Cazador's command. You should follow him. He will save you.
It wouldn't be the worst thing he's ever done to us. You know I'm right, sister.
I have no words. I'm so sorry.
I wish they had.
After these centuries of torment, I know what you all want. More than power. More than to walk in the sun.
Vengeance will taste sweet, paired with Ascension.
Give a sombre look.
Get the hells away from me!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion standing, facing the two vampire spawn that have sneaked into your camp

Text.Value: The world can be a wonderful, kind place, Astarion, when you find a home in it.
I hope we can get some rest now.
Once - in the first decade of my slavery - I found a darling boy who I couldn't bear to bring back to him. So I ran, instead of hurting that sweet man.
Had we killed them, Cazador wouldn't be able to complete the Rite.
Don't act haughty, you're only one tadpole away from being one of them.
You think he's ever kept a promise? He will never let us be free... You all know that.
So don't you ever judge me for doing what Cazador ordered.
A year of silence. Months of scratching my hands raw, trying to carve my way out. More months of not moving at all. Months wishing only for death.
We can save you. Let us help.
You want to see him dead.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player gets up from their bedroll where they've been meditating

Text.Value: For what it's worth, thank you. No matter what happens down there, you helped me stand up against him.
Don't spoil this for me. I almost had them -
Cazador's bond forced their hands against us - can he still force yours?
Easy to say the words, isn't it?
This is our only chance to be free, to end centuries of slavery. You will not ruin it, Astarion!
Move forward, and get your revenge.
We aren't like them. We are better.
That's true. We can say whatever we like, once we're trying to take him back.
We are going to kill him, and anything that gets in our way.
He's going to kill us?
No one ever looked out for me. No one ever said a kind thing to me.
Master Cazador has known where Astarion was this entire time. He knew he would return.
You're slaughter-lambs, all. Cazador needs your souls.
And when he doesn't need you anymore? What then, sister?
I was only teasing you.
Come on, use your pretty heads. The ritual is a sacrifice.
After Cazador caught me, the bastard sealed me, starving, inside a dusty tomb, all on my own, for an entire year.
Because it's more cruel... shit.
Sorry, brother, orders is orders. This is the best we can do.
I'm glad you know.
The bond's hold. He owns us. We have no choice, we must obey. Get out of here, Astarion, before...

EditorData.NodeContext: Last phrase is the moment Cazador takes control of them. They are giving Astarion a final warning to run away.

Text.Value: The master said to take our brother alive. Didn't say anything about you.
He truly broke you.
What a lovely invitation, but I'm afraid I'll have to decline. I intend to kill him, you see?
What a mess. Well, at least you've met my family now.
Attack these new spawn.
Why bother? They seem to like their torturer, now. What does it matter if they end up dead?
Even if they're misled, they're in danger.
Have you no heart, Astarion? You're asking them to die for you in this ritual.
I can't believe how you lied to them. You know they'll have to die for the Rite to happen.
Sorry, sweetheart, but consider our little love affair over. I don't want to be with anyone who has kidnapping fantasies about their partner.
You don't know what it was like. There was no way out.
Runt, we've spoken of vengeance time and again, and you never listened.
And he needs you, Astarion. It's time to come home.
No, he didn't. I am still here. And I will fight him until I fight my last.
Save us? That lickspittle only ever wanted to save himself - the rest of us be damned.
You said they could take me? Really?
You haven't spent much time with my family.
I'm doing this for you, too, you know. To make sure we're both safe. Forever, for good.
How did you find us?
At least you've met my family now.
Of course not, the master's no fool. He needs us.
The Rite... The master needs him. He must attend.
What does Cazador want with him?
Perhaps, but even if this is true, we're bound. We can't disobey him.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player gets up from their bedroll where they've been sleeping

Text.Value: You don't have sympathy for others sharing your plight?
But to steal his life's work... that might be something.
*But if any of the bearers of the scar die before the ritual begins, he will lose his chance to perform the Rite himself.*
Don't look at me like that. With the sweet little 'disappointed I'm not getting cuddly Astarion' pout. I can't take it. I can't be what you want to see in me.

EditorData.NodeContext: really does believe he went too far

Text.Value: And that was your gut response? Really?
The master said 'no witnesses'.
Oh - raagh- RAAAGH-
Enough! Enough talk and enough lies.
This is your chance. Stand with me. Name me your new master. We will get our revenge, and you will all live again.
And while repaying what he did to me is impossible, I am damn well going to steal that bastard's life work. I will become the Ascendant.
Ha! He cannot, thanks to our wriggling friend.
Nothing can make up for that. Not even Cazador's death.
Everything has changed. What matters now is that I can stand up to Cazador.
Our fates were sealed in his writing long ago. A promise to his favourite spawn, fulfilled in the crypt beneath his palace.
'Die' in the ritual? Whatsoever are you speaking of? We are going to cheat undeath.
The Rite of Profane Ascension will be mine, and he won't see a scrap of its glory. I am going to complete the ritual as the Ascendant, and then I am going to kill him.
You're number seven - the final piece of the Rite. He needs us all for the Black Mass.
We have been his servants for centuries, he has always needed us!
I can. I can stop him, but you have to tell me what you know.
Ugh. Well, I suppose you knew we could defeat them. I'll try not to think what would have happened if we hadn't.
Peace, brother. We're here to take you home.
He wouldn't throw away centuries of planning on a scrap like this. They were pulled back just in time.
In turn, what does your life matter?
Was it true what they said? That you gave up fighting him long ago?
Why should we let Cazador have all the fun? After all he's done to us.
I'm doing what I have to... I can't be what you want to see in me.
You were always weak, brother. We don't follow weak.
They mentioned my scars and a rite... I need to get to that crypt and find out what these damn markings are really for.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The spawn have a light glow come over them, begin to feel feral, Cazador's compulsion is coming over them.

Text.Value: Much as we'd love to, the master's orders were very specific.
The master needs all seven of us for the ceremony. Come with us and be reborn. We'll live again.
The master doesn't need to lie to us. He controls us, fully. Why go through the trouble of giving us hope...
We should try to save them, before it's too late.
Stand with the runt of the kennel? The one who always whimpered while he got beat?
You're the only one. Other people don't have a heart like you. You're you. No one is like that.
We're doomed. All right - what do you need from us? We'll help you...
I panicked in the moment!
Master said bring him home. Never forbade us from talking, though.
A few tendays ago, you too would've leapt at the hope that Cazador might free you.
Keep silent.
*You sleep, but the wicked don't. Someone is here to disturb your rest...*
I can't tell whether you're a bad liar or a worse jester, but either way, it isn't cute.
But... perhaps there's something in what you say.
I am rather special, aren't I?
You say, as a mind flayer thrall who spends their life sorting out other people's problems.
Yes. They cannot fight his compulsion. But I can, thanks to our wriggling friend.
*His liar's smile spells danger. He knows full well that his kin will die in the ritual.*
Get away from us!
We will live again, Astarion. The scars on our backs are sealed with the cruellest power. Seven spawn, seven sigils.
Ah, don't sell yourself so short.
Better? What do you mean, 'better'?
Still, you shouldn't have given up.
What does it matter? There's only six of them. And they are vampire spawn.
Listen to me, this ceremony is a mass sacrifice - Cazador is going to kill you all!
And now you think we'll throw away our chance at freedom? By bowing to you?
Oh, I'm well aware of what the master needs. But don't we deserve better?
*He needs them to run willingly to their deaths, thinking they stand a chance against their master.*
This needs to end, one way or another.
Can't we talk this through?
Keep quiet.
Perhaps we can get back at Cazador, and finish the ritual. The seven can unite -

Synopsis: Player and Astarion-companion get attacked by a group of vampire spawns during the night.
